parameters.name: phase
parameters.description:
filter nodes by status

 - POD_PHASE_UNKNOWN: PodUnknown means that for some reason the state of the pod could not be
obtained, typically due to an error in communicating with the host of the
pod.
 - POD_PHASE_PENDING: PodPending means the pod has been accepted by the system, but one or more
of the containers has not been started. This includes time before being
bound to a node, as well as time spent pulling images onto the host.
 - POD_PHASE_RUNNING: PodRunning means the pod has been bound to a node and all of the containers
have been started. At least one container is still running or is in the
process of being restarted. PodSucceeded means that all containers in the
pod have voluntarily terminated with a container exit code of 0, and the
system is not going to restart any of these containers.
 - POD_PHASE_SUCCEED: PodFailed means that all containers in the pod have terminated, and at
least one container has terminated in a failure (exited with a non-zero
exit code or was stopped by the system).
 - POD_PHASE_FAILED: PodFailed means that all containers in the pod have terminated, and at
least one container has terminated in a failure (exited with a non-zero
exit code or was stopped by the system).

parameters.name: spanKinds
parameters.description:
spanKinds is the list of span kinds to include (logical OR) in the
resulting metrics aggregation. Optional. Default = [SPAN_KIND_SERVER].

 - SPAN_KIND_UNSPECIFIED: Unspecified. Do NOT use as default.
Implementations MAY assume SpanKind to be INTERNAL when receiving UNSPECIFIED.
 - SPAN_KIND_INTERNAL: Indicates that the span represents an internal operation within an application,
as opposed to an operation happening at the boundaries. Default value.
 - SPAN_KIND_SERVER: Indicates that the span covers server-side handling of an RPC or other
remote network request.
 - SPAN_KIND_CLIENT: Indicates that the span describes a request to some remote service.
 - SPAN_KIND_PRODUCER: Indicates that the span describes a producer sending a message to a broker.
Unlike CLIENT and SERVER, there is often no direct critical path latency relationship
between producer and consumer spans. A PRODUCER span ends when the message was accepted
by the broker while the logical processing of the message might span a much longer time.
 - SPAN_KIND_CONSUMER: Indicates that the span describes consumer receiving a message from a broker.
Like the PRODUCER kind, there is often no direct critical path latency relationship
between producer and consumer spans.

 - SPAN_KIND_INTERNAL: Indicates that the span represents an internal operation within an application,
as opposed to an operation happening at the boundaries. Default value.
 - SPAN_KIND_SERVER: Indicates that the span covers server-side handling of an RPC or other
remote network request.
 - SPAN_KIND_CLIENT: Indicates that the span describes a request to some remote service.
 - SPAN_KIND_PRODUCER: Indicates that the span describes a producer sending a message to a broker.
Unlike CLIENT and SERVER, there is often no direct critical path latency relationship
between producer and consumer spans. A PRODUCER span ends when the message was accepted
by the broker while the logical processing of the message might span a much longer time.
 - SPAN_KIND_CONSUMER: Indicates that the span describes consumer receiving a message from a broker.
Like the PRODUCER kind, there is often no direct critical path latency relationship
between producer and consumer spans.

availableReplicas 表示可用副本数
requestsPerMinute 请求速率（RPM）
errorRate 错误率（%）
avgLatency 平均延迟（ms）
connections 连接数
receiveBytes 接收吞吐（B/S）

- INTERSECTION: INTERSECTION preform a intersection operation after FilterOperator
 - UNION: UNION preform a union operation after FilterOperator
CURRENT NOT SUPPORT

retentionTime.title: retention_time unit is day, 0 means no need to clean

layer.title: 期望展示的 layer 层级，比如 MESH, TRACING

start.title: start 开始时间 unix timestamp，单位 ms

end.title: end 结束时间 unix timestamp，单位 ms

filters.title:
filters optional. Filter defines some filter operation to the graph data
independently. After filter operators done, there is a collection operation
on filtered graph data depending on filters.agg_type, finally, there is a
dependency fetch operation on the second step result as a root graph to
fetch its dependent data(downstream node or upstream node) from the origin
Graph with dependency_max_depth depth the root node data will have a
property DEPENDENT_TYPE = ROOT the dependency node data will have a
property DEPENDENT_TYPE = DEPENDENT

 - DAOCLOUD_CLUSTER_API: DAOCLOUD_CLUSTER_API indicates a provider of DaoCloud's Cluster API Engine

 - SUSE_RANCHER: SUSE_RANCHER indicates a provider of SUSE Rancher
 - VMWARE_TANZU: VMWARE_TANZU indicates a provider of VMware Tanzu
 - AWS_EKS: 3.Public Cloud
AWS_EKS indicates a provider of AWS EKS
 - ALIYUN_ACK: ALIYUN_ACK indicates a provider of Aliyun ACK
 - TENCENT_TKE: TENCENT_TKE indicates a provider of Tencent TKE.
 - HUAWEI_CCE: TENCENT_TKE indicates a provider of Huawei CCE.
 - MICROSOFT_AZURE: MICROSOFT_AZURE=11; indicates a provider of Microsoft Azure.

lastTransitionTime.title:
Last time the condition transitioned from one status to another.
+optional

lastUpdateTime.title:
Last time we got an update on a given condition.
+optional

message.title:
A human readable message indicating details about the transition.
+optional

reason.title:
The reason for the condition's last transition.
+optional

status.description: Status of the condition, one of True, False, Unknown.

v1alpha1Condition.description: Condition describes the state of a referent at a certain point.

v1alpha1ConditionStatus.description:
These are valid condition statuses.

 - CONDITION_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED: This is only a meaningless placeholder, to avoid zero not return.
 - True: True means a resource is in the condition.
 - False: False means a resource is not in the condition.
 - Unknown: Unknown means kubernetes can't decide if a resource is in the condition or
not.

v1alpha1FilterOperator.title:
- EQ: EQ only support apply on numerical data
= Equality relation between numerics
 - NE: NE only support apply on numerical data
!= Inequality relation between numerics
 - LT: LT only support apply on numerical data
< Less than relation between numerics
 - LE: LE only support apply on numerical data
<= Less than or equal relation between numerics
 - GT: GT only support apply on numerical data
> Greater than relation between numerics
 - GE: GE only support apply on numerical data
>= Greater than or equal relation between numerics
 - CONTAIN: CONTAIN only support apply on string data
RegularExpression
 - NOT_CONTAIN: NOT_CONTAIN only support apply on string data
RegularExpression operation
 - EQUAL: EQUAL only support apply on string data
RegularExpression operation
 - NOT_EQUAL: only support apply on string data
RegularExpression operation
 - REGEX_PATTERN: only support apply on string data
RegularExpression operation

v1alpha1PodPhase.description:
- POD_PHASE_UNKNOWN: PodUnknown means that for some reason the state of the pod could not be
obtained, typically due to an error in communicating with the host of the
pod.
 - POD_PHASE_PENDING: PodPending means the pod has been accepted by the system, but one or more
of the containers has not been started. This includes time before being
bound to a node, as well as time spent pulling images onto the host.
 - POD_PHASE_RUNNING: PodRunning means the pod has been bound to a node and all of the containers
have been started. At least one container is still running or is in the
process of being restarted. PodSucceeded means that all containers in the
pod have voluntarily terminated with a container exit code of 0, and the
system is not going to restart any of these containers.
 - POD_PHASE_SUCCEED: PodFailed means that all containers in the pod have terminated, and at
least one container has terminated in a failure (exited with a non-zero
exit code or was stopped by the system).
 - POD_PHASE_FAILED: PodFailed means that all containers in the pod have terminated, and at
least one container has terminated in a failure (exited with a non-zero
exit code or was stopped by the system).

v1alpha1ServiceType.description:
- SERVICE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED: This is only a meaningless placeholder, to avoid zero not return.
 - CLUSTER_IP: ClusterIP means a service will only be accessible inside the cluster, via
the cluster IP.
 - NODE_PORT: NodePort means a service will be exposed on one port of every node, in
addition to 'ClusterIP' type.
 - LOAD_BALANCER: LoadBalancer means a service will be exposed via an external load balancer
(if the cloud provider supports it), in addition to 'NodePort' type.
 - EXTERNAL_NAME: ExternalName means a service consists of only a reference to an external
name that kubedns or equivalent will return as a CNAME record, with no
exposing or proxying of any pods involved.
v1alpha1ServiceType.title: ServiceType string describes ingress methods for a service

v1alpha1SpanKind.description:
SpanKind is the type of span. Can be used to specify additional relationships between spans
in addition to a parent/child relationship.

 - SPAN_KIND_UNSPECIFIED: Unspecified. Do NOT use as default.
Implementations MAY assume SpanKind to be INTERNAL when receiving UNSPECIFIED.
 - SPAN_KIND_INTERNAL: Indicates that the span represents an internal operation within an application,
as opposed to an operation happening at the boundaries. Default value.
 - SPAN_KIND_SERVER: Indicates that the span covers server-side handling of an RPC or other
remote network request.
 - SPAN_KIND_CLIENT: Indicates that the span describes a request to some remote service.
 - SPAN_KIND_PRODUCER: Indicates that the span describes a producer sending a message to a broker.
Unlike CLIENT and SERVER, there is often no direct critical path latency relationship
between producer and consumer spans. A PRODUCER span ends when the message was accepted
by the broker while the logical processing of the message might span a much longer time.
 - SPAN_KIND_CONSUMER: Indicates that the span describes consumer receiving a message from a broker.
Like the PRODUCER kind, there is often no direct critical path latency relationship
between producer and consumer spans.

timeRanges.description:
if weekday_range is null, start and end is the unix timestamp like
1678350699;
if weekday_range is not null, start and end represents a range
of seconds within a 86400 second day.In this case, start can be greater
than end; For example, 17:00 to End of the day would Start at 61200 and End
at 86400.[default timezone is UTC]
support multiple timerange if weekday_range is not null.

weekdayRange.description:
A list ranges between [0, 6] where 0 = Sunday.
For example: [1,2] means Monday and Tuesday.
[0,1,2,3,4,5,6] means all week.
